periment in June 1984, Campostoma responses were almost identical, and algal standing crop in deeper areas increased significantly after 1 wk. Collectively, our censuses and the experiments indicate that in Brier Creek, biotic interactions strongly influence the pool{\&}{\#}8212;to{\&}{\#}8212;pool distributions of Campostoma and algae, particularly during long periods of constant low discharge. See full-text article at JSTOR},
