ncreases the equilibrium density of plants. But its effect on herbivore density is not predictable without knowledge of the dynamics of the two-species system to which it is added. Addition of the carnivore may not only increase both plant and herbivore densities, it may also stabilize them. Thus, removal of carnivores is a perilous ecological gamble. Because of the nonlinear properties of an exploitative system, measurement of interaction coefficients in one small region of phase space does not yield information about stability in other regions.},
